column5: Check the regs, as there's 2 opening dates for Muskie, 1st Sat and 3rd Sat in June...Not sure if the near to GB lakes are the 1st Sat.

Crane lake/Blackstone are pretty much it around Parry Sound as far as inland lakes. Musky fishing is pretty tough from what I hear. What about heading north a bit? I would fish the Magnetewan river at Britt. Might even be closer for you than going to Crane!
Go to the French river, Hartley bay road. It's only about an hour north.
Magnetewan is not open till the 3rd Sat
Sorry, same for the French, 3rd Saturday.
No need to be sorry, you had better do some research though...
You catch anything at the french there Bawd??
There's no fish in the French come on,..........  ....if you decide to go check for yourself bring an extra prop.
